node.title: Alleged abduction of baby leaves woman critically injured on Gold Coast
node.alt: Side of a Queensland police car in a Brisbane street
node.description: Police find a woman unresponsive in a Gold Coast apartment and allege a baby was taken before being found hours later.Â
node.content: ["A 34-year-old man has been charged in relation to the serious assault of a woman on the Gold Coast that police say was linked to the alleged abduction of an 11-month-old boy.\u00a0", "Police were called to an apartment complex in Como Crescent in Southport at about 5pm yesterday after reports of a disturbance.", "After arriving, officers found a 25-year-old woman unresponsive in one of the apartments.", "She was taken to the Gold Coast University Hospital with life-threatening injuries and remains in a critical condition.", "A crime scene was established at the apartment.", "Police will allege that an 11-month-old baby boy was taken from the address, sparking an Amber Alert.", "The infant was found safe and well at about midnight \u2014\u00a0about seven hours after the alert was issued.", "Just over half an hour after the baby was located, a 34-year-old man from the Logan suburb of Crestmead was arrested at Oxley in Brisbane's south-west.\u00a0", "Police said they had seized a grey SUV as part of the investigation into the matter.", "The man faces charges of grievous bodily harm and strangulation.\u00a0", "He is due to face Richlands Magistrates Court tomorrow."]
